Note that you can improve Word .doc and LibreOffice .odt import and export by installing Java on your machine. This allows Scrivener to take advantage of more advanced converters for these formats.

If enabled, Scrivener will use the same Java-based converters for .docx as it uses for .doc and .odt formats. There should never be any need to turn this on unless you run into problems with .docx conversion (if so, please report the issues to us).
The theme will be saved in Scrivener's Application Support folder and will be available in the "Manage..." and "Scrivener" menus.
